x any remaining docs issues\n\nActually wait - let me re-read the review more ca
refully. It says the BDD step definitions "全部为空实现". But looking at the cod
e, they have actual implementations. However, they wrap `test` with `skip`. So t
echnically the tests are skipped and don\'t verify anything. I should remove the
skip wrapper.\n\nBut there\'s another issue: the BDD tests mock repos directly b
ut may not actually work because `getServer()` might not provide those mocks. Le
t me check the bdd-setup file.\n\nAlso, looking at the GetConversationsQueryDto 
and GetMessagesQueryDto again:\n- `GetConversationsQueryDto.cursor` has `@IsInt(
)` but conversation cursor is a date ISO string\n- `GetMessagesQueryDto.cursor` 
has `@IsInt()` but message cursor is a sequence_id string\n\nActually, looking a
t `GetMessagesQueryDto`, `cursor` is typed as `string` but decorated with `@IsIn
t()`. This is contradictory - the type is string but validator says int. When Va
lidationPipe transforms, `@Type(() => Number)` will try to convert the string to
a number, and `@IsInt()` will validate it as a number. But the controller passes
it as a string to the service (`query.cursor`), and the service does `parseInt(c
ursor, 10)`.\n\nWait, looking at the controller:\n```typescript\nconst data = aw
ait this.imService.getMessages(\n  user.userId,\n  query.conversation_id,\n  que
ry.cursor,\n  query.limit,\n);\n```\n\nAnd in `im.service.ts`:\n```typescript\ni
f (cursor) {\n  const cursorNum = parseInt(cursor, 10);\n  if (!isNaN(cursorNum)
) {\n    qb.andWhere("m.sequence_id < :cursor", { cursor: cursorNum });\n  }\n}\
n```\n\nSo cursor is passed as a string to the service. If the DTO converts it t
o a number with `@Type(() => Number)`, then `query.cursor` would be a number, an
d the service `parseInt(cursor, 10)` would still work. But the DTO definition sa
ys `cursor?: string` while decorators say `@IsInt() @Type(() => Number)`. That\'
s inconsistent.\n\nFor `GetConversationsQueryDto`, cursor is a date string like 
`2025-04-26T10:00:00.000Z`. `@IsInt()` and `@Type(() => Number)` would incorrect
ly try to validate/convert it as a number.\n\nFor both DTOs, cursor should just 
be `@IsOptional() @IsString()` without `@Type(() => Number)`. And for `GetConver
sationsQueryDto`, definitely remove `@IsInt()`.\n\nActually, looking at the `Get
MessagesQueryDto` type: `cursor?: string;` but with `@IsInt() @Type(() => Number
)`. This is clearly wrong. The `GetConversationsQueryDto` also has `cursor?: str
ing;` with `@IsInt() @Type(() => Number)`.\n\nLet me fix these.\n\nNow let me ch
eck the bdd-setup to understand if the BDD tests can actually run.',
    encrypted=None
)
