ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='The tests are timing out because the bloc doesn\'t emit anything when
we add `ReceiveMessage` with `ImInitial` state. Looking at the bloc code:\n\n```
dart\nFuture<void> _onReceiveMessage(\n  ReceiveMessage event,\n  Emitter<ImStat
e> emit,\n) async {\n  if (event.message.conversationId != _currentConversationI
d) {\n    _pendingMessages.putIfAbsent(...).add(event.message);\n    return;\n  
}\n\n  if (state is! MessagesLoaded && state is! MessageSending && state is! Mes
sageSent) {\n    return;\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nWhen the state is `ImInitial` (t
he initial state), `_onReceiveMessage` just returns without emitting anything. S
o the `expectLater` waits forever for an emission that never comes.\n\nI need to
fix the tests to first establish a `MessagesLoaded` state before testing message
reception. I can do this by:\n1. Mocking `repository.getMessages` to return data
\n2. Adding `LoadMessages` event first\n3. Then testing `ReceiveMessage`\n\nOr, 
for simpler tests, I can directly add a `ReceiveMessage` only after `LoadMessage
s` has established state.\n\nLet me rewrite the failing tests to properly set up
state first.\n\nAlso, for the "updates message status to sent on ack" test, the 
issue is that `ReceiveMessage` is called when state is `ImInitial`, so it return
s early. I need to first load messages to establish `MessagesLoaded` state.\n\nL
et me fix the test file.',
    encrypted=None
)
