ageRepo.save` mock in bdd-setup.js always returns a generated id with sequence_i
d 1. So both POST calls return different ids (well, actually the same generated 
values since the mock is deterministic). But the test expects them to be the sam
e.\n\nWait, looking at bdd-setup.js:\n```javascript\nsave: jest.fn().mockImpleme
ntation((data) =>\n  Promise.resolve({\n    ...(data || {}),\n    id: data?.id |
| \'msg-generated-id\',\n    sequence_id: data?.sequence_id || 1,\n    created_a
t: data?.created_at || new Date(),\n  }),\n),\n```\n\nIf `data.id` is provided (
which it is, from `uuidv7()` in the service), then `id` would be the same as `da
ta.id`. But `uuidv7()` generates different IDs each time. However, in the mock, 
`messageRepo.create` returns `data` (which includes the id), and then `messageRe
po.save` receives that data.\n\nWait, looking at `im.service.ts`:\n```typescript
\nconst message = this.messageRepo.create({\n  id: uuidv7(),\n  ...\n});\nconst 
saved = await this.messageRepo.save(message);\n```\n\nIn the mock:\n- `create` r
eturns the data passed to it (which includes `id: uuidv7()`)\n- `save` receives 
that data and returns `{ ...data, id: data.id, sequence_id: data.sequence_id || 
1, ... }`\n\nBut `uuidv7()` is a real function that generates different IDs each
time. So both POST calls would generate different IDs, and the test would fail b
ecause `firstResponse.body.data.id !== secondResponse.body.data.id`.\n\nFor the 
duplicate test to work, I need to:\n1. Make `messageRepo.save` throw a duplicate
error on the second call with the same `client_message_id`\n2. Make `messageRepo
.findOne` return the existing message when queried by `conversation_id` and `cli
ent_message_id`\n\nBut the mock `messageRepo.save` doesn\'t have access to previ
ous calls to check for duplicates. And `messageRepo.findOne` isn\'t set up to re
turn anything specific.\n\nA simpler approach: I can mock `messageRepo.save` to 
check if the data has been seen before, and if so, throw a duplicate error. And 
I can mock `messageRepo.findOne` to return the first saved message when queried.
\n\nBut this requires shared state between mocks, which is tricky.\n\nAlternativ
